headline.main: WINSON EXCELLED IN FEDERAL POSTS; Won Distinction in Congress, as Executive and Jurist -- Noted as a Conciliator

abstract: career; illus taking oath as Chief Justice, '46
snippet: Fred M. Vinson enjoyed a note-worthy career in each of the three branches of the Federal Government -- legislative, executive and judicial. In twelve years in the House of Representatives he won wide renown as a tax and fiscal expert.
